detailing how terrible
everything is and how

00:55:45.350 --> 00:55:47.999
they'll definitely repay you
with a car or something--

00:55:47.999 --> 00:55:48.790
DAN JURAFSKY: Yeah.

00:55:48.790 --> 00:55:49.290
Yes.

00:55:52.690 --> 00:55:55.760
Basically the question is, is it
linear, or is there a ceiling,

00:55:55.760 --> 00:55:57.790
or is it is there an
inverse u-shaped curve

00:55:57.790 --> 00:56:00.079
where if it gets too
long it dies out.

00:56:00.079 --> 00:56:00.620
I don't know.

00:56:00.620 --> 00:56:02.054
We didn't look for that.

00:56:02.054 --> 00:56:03.470
We just looked for
the main effect

00:56:03.470 --> 00:56:05.440
and there's clearly a
main effective of length

00:56:05.440 --> 00:56:07.300
and evidentially but
it could very well

